TechWeek Event Registration Terms and Conditions*

By opting-in you agree that Yahoo, and its participating partners and/or sponsors, may use your data to contact you with information about related products and services.  If you provide your data directly to the partner or sponsor, you agree to the partner or sponsor’s privacy policy and terms of service.  If you provide your data to Yahoo, you agree to Yahoo’s Privacy Policy and Yahoo’s Terms of Service.  GDPR: For EU residents, please visit the Yahoo EMEA Privacy Policy to learn more about the data that Yahoo collects, the purposes for collection, and your rights in relation to such data.  CCPA Notice at Collection: For California consumers, please visit the Yahoo California Privacy Rights page to learn more about the categories of personal information Yahoo collects and the purposes for collection. Sponsor’s privacy policies are located at:  RedHat, Intel, SuperMicro, and AWS.

Yahoo is not responsible for the content or accuracy of speakers’ statements, presentations, or sessions, including any expert or professional content provided during the event.  The views and opinions expressed by speakers are their own and do not reflect the opinions of, or imply an endorsement or recommendation, by Yahoo.  You are responsible for reviewing all information and performing your own diligence before taking any actions with respect to the speaker’s topic.

The event is voluntary and you assume risk, including bodily injury, in connection with your participation, in person or virtually. To extent permitted by law, you hereby forever release Yahoo and its affiliates from any and all actions, claims, or demands that you may have in the future, including without limitation any and all claims and causes of action against Yahoo for loss of or damage to property and for injuries to or death of persons in connection with the event.

You acknowledge that the event will be live streamed and/or recorded (including without limitation, photographed, audiotaped, videotaped, filmed, or recorded in written form) and may be made available for later viewing (in Yahoo’s sole discretion).  You acknowledge that all event activities and attendees may be included in such recordings and by participating in the event(s), You irrevocably consent to being recorded in the manner set forth above and simultaneously live streamed/broadcast, and release Yahoo and users of such recordings from liability or loss or damage to persons or property or for infringement of any rights.  Further, you expressly authorize and permit use of your name, likeness and voice and all reproductions thereof throughout the world in perpetuity without limitation and without any compensation.  You acknowledge that Yahoo is the exclusive owner of the live stream and recordings and any proceeds related thereto.  The live stream and recordings are for Yahoo’s use only.  You agree not to make your own recordings of the event.

You agree to comply with rules established by Yahoo, the venue, or the virtual event platform provider as the case may be, including without limitation health and safety protocols, such as COVID prevention measures and contact tracing.

You agree not to disclose, disseminate or otherwise publish or communicate information that is, or is reasonably understood to be, confidential or proprietary to Yahoo, which shall include, without limitation, information received in connection with the event (including without limitation Yahoo products or services, inventions, ideas, developments, discoveries, product formulae, software, drawings, procedures, processes, specifications, reports, notes, documents, plans, reports, and improvements).  You agree that Yahoo has the right to seek injunctive relief, in addition to any other legal remedies available at law or in equity, for your breach of confidentiality.
